%N A121849 The spiral parameter epsilon for the icosahedral fullerenes.
%C A121849 Icosahedral fullerenes are ordered by increasing number of carbon atoms, then increasing Goldberg parameter i, and finally increasing Goldberg parameter j. For parameters 0 <= j <= i, then corresponding number of carbon atoms is m = 20 * (i^2 + i*j + j^2). - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jul 13 2026
%H A121849 P. W. Fowler and K. M. Rogers, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1021/ci9901486">Spiral Codes and Goldberg Representations of Icosahedral Fullerenes and Octahedral Analogues</a>, J. Chem. Inf. Comput. Sci., vol. 41 (2001) 108-111.
%F A121849 a(n) = (5/2)*i^2 + (15/2)*j^2 - (3/2)*i - (7/2)*j - i*delta_{j0} where i and j are the Goldberg parameters [see Fowler and Rogers]. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jul 13 2026
%e A121849 If m=80 then the parameter epsilon is 5.
%e A121849 If m=500 then the parameter epsilon is 50.
%Y A121849 Cf. A121847, A121848.
